gsb high tech club blog archive harvard's new print on demand machine stanford university gsb high tech club official website of the gsb high tech club harvard's new print on demand machine home new technologies harvard's new print on demand machine rumor says ea is to acquire playfish for $250 m high tech club has a new website gsbhightechclub stanford edu gsb high tech clubbers should take the lead for transforming stanford bookstore as well harvard book store has cut the ribbon on the brand new print on demand machine on sep 29th the machine will print from a catalog of 3.6 million books and it is capable of printing a 300 page book in 4 minutes after hundreds of years of silence the print domain has started its evolution with ereaders eg kindle and is continuing with the efforts of google books and universities like harvard it will be interesting to see what print on demand books will mean for greenhouse gases due to reduced logistics costs royalties & copyrights and literacy around the world this entry was posted on wednesday october 14th 2009 at 11 35 pm and is filed under new technologies you can follow any responses to this entry through the rss 2.0 feed both comments and pings are currently closed comments are closed gsb high tech club is proudly powered by wordpress entries rss and comments rss stanford university 450 serra mall stanford california 94305 650 723 2300 terms of use copyright complaints
